<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-jgnm-f4zP3WLhlWyPS1cEQ" name="Develop design and coding guidelines,_xKfWAKGJEeC6D4cw2ululQ" guid="-jgnm-f4zP3WLhlWyPS1cEQ" changeDate="2011-08-24T05:06:21.506-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The design and coding guidelines need to take a number of characteristics into account based upon the tool selection,&#xD;
    methods used and whether a programming language or modeling language is used for the development of the software.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The user needs to be aware that different programming languages have different coding guidelines, the same also applies&#xD;
    for modeling languages. It might also be necessary to modify existing guidelines for specific item development.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Please refer to &quot;Table 1, Topics to be covered by modeling and coding guidelines&quot; in Volume 6, clause 5.4.6 of the&#xD;
    standard for detailed information about specific guidance on the ASIL level recommendations (++,+ or O). The best&#xD;
    practices covered are the following:&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Enforcement of low complexity&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Use of language subsets&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Enforcement of strong typing&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Use of defensive implementation techniques&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Use of established design principles&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Use of ambiguous graphical representation&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Use of style guides&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Use of naming conventions&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To ensure that the developers are working to&amp;nbsp;common guidelines&amp;nbsp;so that the code&amp;nbsp;(or model, if using models&#xD;
based)&amp;nbsp;is understandable and conforms to standard best practice depending upon the methods, language and process to be&#xD;
used.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
